From: bluecat <lmhtq1991@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 29 May 2026 14:05:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] Phase C-6 L42 (partial): cap-LDR for resolved field/method metadata + STRUCTURAL finding

Mechanical part (correct, necessary): load_field_cp_cache_entry's
is_static f1 (holder Klass*) + java_mirror loads, and
load_invoke_cp_cache_entry's resolved Method* load, are capabilities —
switched from integer ldr to cap-LDR.

STRUCTURAL blocker discovered (the real L42): ConstantPoolCacheEntry on
CHERI purecap is 48 bytes, NOT 32:
    _indices intx      @0   (8)
    _f1      Metadata*  @16  (16-byte CAP, 16-byte aligned → 8B pad after _indices)
    _f2      intx       @32  (8)
    _flags   intx       @40  (8)   → sizeof = 48 (cap-aligned), NON-power-of-2.

But the interpreter hardcodes the entry stride as `lsl #5` (×32) — e.g.
get_cache_and_index_at_bcp line 225 `add(cache, rcpool, index, LSL, 5)`
and templateTable codegen. For cpcache index 0 the stride is irrelevant
(works), but for any index != 0 it points into the wrong/mid entry, so
f1 reads back NULL and the subsequent cap-LDR of the java_mirror
dereferences null → fault. The asserts that would have caught this
(sizeof == 4*wordSize == 32; exact_log2(size) == 2+LogBytesPerWord)
are compiled out in this optimized build.

This is a class-3 (layout/size mismatch) issue, not a mechanical
cap-LDR sweep. The fix needs deliberate structural work: pad
ConstantPoolCacheEntry to a power-of-2 (64 bytes) on CHERI and update
every hardcoded ×32 stride to ×64, OR replace the shift with a computed
×sizeof multiply, then re-verify all f1/f2/flags offsets. Deferred to a
focused next session — documented in docs/36.

Session: 41 commits, 104 build iterations, L25-L41 resolved, L42
characterized as a structural cpcache-layout issue.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>

diff --git a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/templateTable_aarch64.cpp b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/templateTable_aarch64.cpp
index 4666b42b933..4b2873dd9b0 100644
--- a/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/templateTable_aarch64.cpp
+++ b/src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/templateTable_aarch64.cpp
@@ -2299,10 +2299,18 @@ void TemplateTable::load_field_cp_cache_entry(Register obj,
 
   // klass overwrite register
   if (is_static) {
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+    // C-6 fix #42: f1 (holder Klass*) and the java_mirror are caps;
+    // integer ldr strips the tag and the following deref faults.
+    __ cap_ldr_imm(obj, cache, in_bytes(cp_base_offset +
+                                        ConstantPoolCacheEntry::f1_offset()));
+    __ cap_ldr_imm(obj, obj, in_bytes(Klass::java_mirror_offset()));
+#else
     __ ldr(obj, Address(cache, in_bytes(cp_base_offset +
                                         ConstantPoolCacheEntry::f1_offset())));
     const int mirror_offset = in_bytes(Klass::java_mirror_offset());
     __ ldr(obj, Address(obj, mirror_offset));
+#endif
     __ resolve_oop_handle(obj);
   }
 }
@@ -2336,9 +2344,17 @@ void TemplateTable::load_invoke_cp_cache_entry(int byte_no,
 
   size_t index_size = (is_invokedynamic ? sizeof(u4) : sizeof(u2));
   resolve_cache_and_index(byte_no, cache, index, index_size);
+#ifdef __CHERI_PURE_CAPABILITY__
+  // C-6 fix #42: the resolved Method* (f1, or f2 for invokevirtual) is a
+  // cap; integer ldr strips the tag and dispatch faults.
+  __ cap_ldr_imm(method, cache, method_offset);
+#else
   __ ldr(method, Address(cache, method_offset));
+#endif
 
   if (itable_index != noreg) {
+    // itable_index comes from f2: a plain integer index (vtable/itable
+    // slot) for the virtual/interface case — an integer load is correct.
     __ ldr(itable_index, Address(cache, index_offset));
   }
   __ ldrw(flags, Address(cache, flags_offset));
